figure Security.txt in Magento 2 03\"/></noscript><script type=\"module\">const t=\"undefined\"!=typeof HTMLImageElement&&\"loading\"in HTMLImageElement.prototype;if(t){const t=document.querySelectorAll(\"img[data-main-image]\");for(let e of t){e.dataset.src&&(e.setAttribute(\"src\",e.dataset.src),e.removeAttribute(\"data-src\")),e.dataset.srcset&&(e.setAttribute(\"srcset\",e.dataset.srcset),e.removeAttribute(\"data-srcset\"));const t=e.parentNode.querySelectorAll(\"source[data-srcset]\");for(let e of t)e.setAttribute(\"srcset\",e.dataset.srcset),e.removeAttribute(\"data-srcset\");e.complete&&(e.style.opacity=1,e.parentNode.parentNode.querySelector(\"[data-placeholder-image]\").style.opacity=0)}}</script></div><script type=\"application/json\" data-wp-inline-image-hydration=\"3\">{\"image\":{\"images\":{\"sources\":[],\"fallback\":{\"src\":\"/_gatsby/image/7517958fef9efa13b47cd08f306fbfdd/8345e81ae9f7c695928866c71580d156/How-to-Configure-Security.txt-in-Magento-2-03.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Configure-Security.txt-in-Magento-2-03.png&a=w%3D136%26h%3D147%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-15T06%3A02%3A29\",\"srcSet\":\"/_gatsby/image/7517958fef9efa13b47cd08f306fbfdd/8345e81ae9f7c695928866c71580d156/How-to-Configure-Security.txt-in-Magento-2-03.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Configure-Security.txt-in-Magento-2-03.png&a=w%3D136%26h%3D147%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-15T06%3A02%3A29 136w,/_gatsby/image/7517958fef9efa13b47cd08f306fbfdd/447241f359b2550ccaf95781eb33a891/How-to-Configure-Security.txt-in-Magento-2-03.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Configure-Security.txt-in-Magento-2-03.png&a=w%3D272%26h%3D293%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-15T06%3A02%3A29 272w,/_gatsby/image/7517958fef9efa13b47cd08f306fbfdd/25bf9887aeb242ed4bebcae2f44cc71c/How-to-Configure-Security.txt-in-Magento-2-03.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Configure-Security.txt-in-Magento-2-03.png&a=w%3D543%26h%3D585%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-15T06%3A02%3A29 543w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 543px) 543px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":543,\"height\":585},\"alt\":\"How to Configure Security.txt in Magento 2 03\",\"className\":\"wp-image-1452 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"3\"}</script></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Note: Keep acknowledgments brief and general, avoiding detailed information about security issues.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Specify your Preferred Languages</strong> &#8211; for security reports using two-letter language symbols separated by commas. Provide a link to your&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Hiring</strong> &#8211; page for security positions on your website.&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Policy</strong> &#8211; Give a URL for your security Policy page.&nbsp;</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Signature</strong> &#8211; Attach a link to the file containing your digital Signature.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>To create the signature file, run the following command in the command line:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><em>gpg -u KEYID --output security.txt.sig --armor --detach-sig security.txt</em></code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Ensure to save the signature file on the server in the .well-known folder.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5. To configure security.txt in Magento 2, follow these steps:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li> Create a file with all security-related information.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Make sure to press the &#8220;Save Config&#8221; button.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s all you need to do to set up security.txt. This reporting channel ensures that security vulnerabilities in your store will not go unnoticed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note: This should not be your only means of ensuring the security of your store. Be sure to implement the best Magento admin security practices to prevent vulnerabilities from arising in the first place.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The proper configuration of security.txt and <a href=\"/how-to-install-modules-manually-in-magento-2/\">manual installation of modules</a> are both crucial for ensuring the security and efficiency of a Magento 2 store. By following the steps to configure security.txt, you can establish a reporting channel for security vulnerabilities, while manual module installation can provide additional functionality and customization. It is important to regularly assess and implement recommended security measures to maintain the safety and integrity of your online platform.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div class='sf_fb_share sf_icon' style='text-align:left;vertical-align: middle;'><a  target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=/how-to-configure-security-txt-in-magento-2/' style='display:inline-block;'><img class='sfsi_wicon'  data-pin-nopin='true' alt='fb-share-icon' title='Facebook Share' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/fb_icons/en_US.svg' /></a></div><div class='sf_twiter sf_icon' style='display: inline-block;vertical-align: middle;width: auto;margin-left: 7px;'>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=How+to+Configure+Security.txt+in+Magento+2%3F+https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fhow-to-configure-security-txt-in-magento-2%2F'style='display:inline-block' >\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img data-pin-nopin= true class='sfsi_wicon' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/Twitter_Tweet/en_US_Tweet.svg' alt='Tweet' title='Tweet' >\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</a>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div></div></div><